🚀 Microservices Node.js App with Docker & CI/CD

This repository contains a production-ready microservices-based application built with Node.js. Each service is containerized using Docker and orchestrated for seamless deployment.

The project follows modern DevOps practices, implementing a CI/CD pipeline with GitHub Actions to ensure automated builds, tests, and deployments.

🔑 Key Features

⚡ Microservices Architecture – Independent, loosely coupled Node.js services.

🐳 Dockerized Services – Each service runs in its own container.

🔄 API Gateway – Centralized entry point for routing and load balancing.

🛠 CI/CD with GitHub Actions – Automated testing, linting, and deployment workflows.

📦 Scalability & Maintainability – Easy to scale services independently.

🔐 Environment Configuration – Secure handling of secrets and environment variables.

🛠 Tech Stack

Backend: Node.js (Express / Nest.js)

Database: MongoDB / PostgreSQL (per service)

Containers: Docker, Docker Compose

CI/CD: GitHub Actions

Messaging (optional): RabbitMQ / Kafka for async communication

📂 Project Highlights

✅ Code Quality ensured with ESLint + Prettier

✅ Unit & Integration tests with Jest / Mocha

✅ GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD

✅ Ready-to-deploy Docker images